---
title: SpacesSync — runtime sync workflow (ROADMAP v3 — verify-based, no arbitrary waits)
---
flowchart TD
    classDef user fill:#1e3a5f,stroke:#4a90e2,stroke-width:2px,color:#fff
    classDef macos fill:#3a3a3a,stroke:#888,stroke-width:1.5px,color:#eee
    classDef spoon fill:#1f4d2e,stroke:#4caf50,stroke-width:1.5px,color:#fff
    classDef new fill:#1f3a4d,stroke:#4ab3c6,stroke-width:2px,color:#fff
    classDef decision fill:#5a4a1e,stroke:#d4a853,stroke-width:1.5px,color:#fff
    classDef terminal fill:#4a1f1f,stroke:#e57373,stroke-width:1.5px,color:#fff
    classDef ui fill:#3d2a4d,stroke:#b07cc6,stroke-width:1.5px,color:#fff

    %% ============================================================
    %% READING NOTE
    %% ============================================================
    %% v3 differs from CURRENT in three structural ways:
    %% 1. Two entry paths instead of one — the spaces-watcher path
    %%    (user swipes) and a new screen-watcher path (display reconfig).
    %% 2. The sync chain uses fire-and-verify instead of fire-and-wait.
    %%    The fixed switchDelay and debounceSeconds are gone.
    %% 3. Per-target lastActiveSpaces writes happen AFTER each poll-verify,
    %%    using the OBSERVED post-poll value (Q1 resolution; F-010 §6.2).
    %%    Echoes get absorbed without a debounce window because the
    %%    baseline always matches what macOS just confirmed.
    %% Each node opens with a <b>bold lead</b> for quick-skim.
    %% Detail follows for the deeper reader.
    %% ============================================================

    %% ============================================================
    %% KEY CONCEPTS — read this first
    %% ============================================================
    KEY["<div style='text-align: left;'><b>Key concepts — read this first</b><br/><br/>• <b>Space</b> — a macOS virtual desktop on a single display. Each display has its own list.<br/>• <b>Sync group</b> — a list of displays that should track each other. When any one switches Space, the others follow.<br/>• <b>Trigger display</b> — the display the user actually switched. <b>Target display</b> — another display in the same sync group that we drive to match.<br/>• <b>Spaces watcher</b> = hs.spaces.watcher. Fires on Space changes — primary entry path.<br/>• <b>Screen watcher</b> = hs.screen.watcher. <i>(new in v3)</i> Fires on display layout changes (plug/unplug, lid open/close, rearrange) — second entry path.<br/>• <b>gotoSpace</b> = hs.spaces.gotoSpace. Dispatch only — v3 verifies via polling rather than waiting an arbitrary time.<br/>• <b>lastActiveSpaces</b> — snapshot of prior per-display Space state. <i>v3 writes it per target after each poll-verify</i>, using the observed post-poll value (Q1; F-010 §6.2). Echoes naturally diff to no-change.<br/>• <b>syncInProgress</b> — boolean. true during the chain's polling window. v3 window ≈ actual chain duration; v0.2 window was chain + debounce padding (~1.7s for 4 displays).<br/>• <b>pollTimeout</b> — upper bound on waiting for a single gotoSpace to verify. ~2 s (F-010 §6.1). Replaces fixed switchDelay.</div>"]:::keybox
    classDef keybox fill:#0d1a26,stroke:#4ab3c6,color:#cfe6f0,text-align:left

    %% ============================================================
    %% ENTRY PATH 1 — USER SWIPE → SPACES WATCHER
    %% ============================================================

    U(["<b>User switches a Space.</b><br/>Via Mission Control gesture, ⌃→/⌃←,<br/>a Dock click, or other macOS UI."]):::user
    OS["<b>macOS commits the switch.</b><br/>The chosen Space is now active on that display."]:::macos
    W["<b>Spaces watcher fires our callback.</b><br/>hs.spaces.watcher invokes our Lua callback —<br/>the signal that a Space somewhere changed."]:::macos

    GATE_ENABLED{"<b>Is SpacesSync enabled?</b><br/>(false after the user toggles off via the<br/>toggle hotkey or :stop)"}:::decision
    SKIP_DISABLED[/"<b>Return — SpacesSync is off.</b><br/>How we got here: user pressed the toggle hotkey<br/>(default ⌃⌥⌘Y), or called spoon.SpacesSync:stop()<br/>from init.lua, the Hammerspoon console, or hs -c.<br/><br/>Why we still need this guard: when :stop runs,<br/>macOS may already be partway through calling our<br/>watcher function. You can't kill an in-flight call —<br/>so this guard makes that one straggler bail out<br/>instead of finishing a sync the user just stopped."/]:::terminal

    GATE_RUNNING{"<b>Already running a sync chain?</b><br/>syncInProgress == true while we are dispatching<br/>and polling for verification of gotoSpace calls."}:::decision
    DROP[/"<b>Drop the event.</b><br/>Whole point of syncInProgress: swallow our own<br/>gotoSpace echoes that fire while we're still polling.<br/><br/>Window length in v3 = sum of per-target poll times.<br/>(Targets = sync-group size − 1; trigger excluded.)<br/>Typical case: numTargets × ~750 ms (F-010 mean) — for<br/>a 4-display group (3 targets), ~2.3 s typical (about 35% longer<br/>than v0.2's 1.7 s ceiling, but driven by actual macOS settle<br/>rather than an arbitrary clock — slightly slower in exchange<br/>for not silently dropping calls when macOS is slow).<br/>Worst case: numTargets × pollTimeout (2 s) = 6 s for 4 displays<br/>if every dispatch hits its timeout — strictly worse than v0.2.<br/>The trade is reliability over fixed-bound: typical case ≈ v0.2;<br/>pathological case slower; correctness much better.<br/><br/>Real user swipes inside this window are still dropped."/]:::terminal

    DIFF["<b>Diff to find what changed.</b><br/>Compare hs.spaces.activeSpaces against lastActiveSpaces<br/>to find which display(s) just switched."]:::spoon
    FIND{"<b>Did anything actually change?</b><br/>Did at least one display's active Space change<br/>since the last snapshot?<br/><br/>Note: if multiple displays changed in the same<br/>watcher fire, only the FIRST one found becomes the trigger.<br/>The others are folded into the baseline silently.<br/>(See OmniFocus task on multi-changed handling.)"}:::decision
    NO_CHANGE["<b>No actual Space change — exit.</b><br/>The watcher fires on more than real Space switches:<br/>Mission Control opening, animation settling,<br/>Stage Manager events. The diff confirms nothing<br/>actually changed — refresh the snapshot defensively<br/>and exit. <i>v3 also reaches this from gotoSpace echoes</i><br/><i>because the per-target observed-value writes already</i><br/><i>updated the baseline to match macOS's confirmed state.</i>"]:::spoon

    LOOKUP["<b>Find the trigger's sync group.</b><br/>Map the trigger display's UUID → position number,<br/>then scan syncGroups for a group containing that position."]:::spoon
    GROUP{"<b>Trigger in a sync group?</b><br/>Is the trigger display a member of any group?"}:::decision

    INDEPENDENT["<b>Independent display — nothing to sync.</b><br/>Trigger is not in any sync group.<br/>We dispatch zero gotoSpace calls on this path,<br/>so there are no echoes to worry about — which is<br/>why we don't need syncInProgress here."]:::spoon

    LOCK["<b>Set syncInProgress = true; bump chainGeneration.</b> <i>(council mitigation)</i><br/>From now until the chain's verifier completes,<br/>spaces-watcher fires are dropped. The chainGeneration<br/>integer is captured by every poll/dispatch closure;<br/>BAIL_CHAIN, :stop, and the watchdog all bump it,<br/>so any in-flight closure can detect 'I was bailed'<br/>and exit before doing further damage."]:::spoon

    COMPUTE_EXPECTED["<b>Compute the expected end state.</b> <i>(new in v3)</i><br/>Snapshot hs.spaces.activeSpaces; this is the starting world.<br/>For each target in the sync group, replace its entry with<br/>the Space ID at the trigger's index on that target.<br/><br/>The result is a per-display UUID → Space ID map describing<br/>exactly what we want the world to look like when the chain finishes.<br/>This single map drives both the per-target dispatches during<br/>the chain AND the verification at chain end — one source of truth.<br/>(Note: per Q1 the per-target lastActiveSpaces writes use the<br/>OBSERVED post-poll value, not the value from this map.)"]:::new

    SYNCNEXT[/"<b>Iterate target displays.</b><br/>Targets = sync-group members minus the trigger.<br/>Start at i = 1."/]:::spoon

    %% --- v3 NEW: fire-and-verify replaces fire-and-wait ---
    DISPATCH["<b>Dispatch hs.spaces.gotoSpace.</b><br/>Look up the target's expected Space ID from<br/>expectedEndState[targetUUID] (computed at chain start),<br/>then call gotoSpace. macOS animates the switch."]:::spoon
    POLL["<b>Poll for verification.</b> <i>(replaces switchDelay in v3)</i><br/>Every ~30 ms, re-read hs.spaces.activeSpaceOnScreen(target).<br/>Continue when it matches the expected Space ID,<br/>OR pollTimeout (~2 s) elapses — whichever comes first.<br/>Each poll iteration also re-checks state.enabled and<br/>chainGeneration; bails if either changed.<br/><br/>Calibrated via F-010 polling spike: Model B holds —<br/>activeSpaceOnScreen flips at end of MC animation,<br/>so polling alone is a sufficient ready signal.<br/>Mean flip latency 753 ms; pollTimeout 2 s covers slow settle."]:::new
    VERIFY{"<b>Did the target reach the expected Space?</b><br/>If yes — verified, move on.<br/>If no (poll timeout) — macOS dropped the dispatch<br/>or settle was unexpectedly slow."}:::decision
    DROPPED_LOG["<b>Log dispatch drop.</b><br/>Warning level: 'target X: gotoSpace did not land<br/>within pollTimeout.' Don't block the chain —<br/>continue to OBSERVED_WRITE so the baseline reflects<br/>macOS's actual stuck state, not a lie."]:::new

    OBSERVED_WRITE["<b>Write observed value to baseline.</b> <i>(Q1 resolution, new in v3)</i><br/>Read activeSpaceOnScreen(target) once more<br/>and set state.lastActiveSpaces[targetUUID] = observed.<br/><br/>On success: observed == expected (the dispatch landed).<br/>On poll timeout: observed == macOS's actual stuck state<br/>(end-of-chain verifier will surface this as drift).<br/><br/>Either way, the baseline matches reality — echoes that<br/>arrive after this point diff to no-change naturally;<br/>no debounce window needed. (Per F-010 §6.2: cheaper<br/>than pre-dispatch expected-value writes, and can't poison<br/>the baseline if macOS dropped the call.)"]:::new

    MORE{"<b>More targets?</b><br/>Any target displays remaining in the sync group?<br/><br/>Note: no inter-dispatch wait. F-010 confirmed Model B<br/>(160/160 dispatches at gap=0); polling is sufficient."}:::decision

    VERIFY_END_STATE["<b>Verify world matches expected end state.</b> <i>(scoped to sync-group path)</i><br/>Read actual = hs.spaces.activeSpaces.<br/>Diff against expectedEndState (computed at chain start).<br/>The diff covers EVERY display in expectedEndState —<br/>sync-group members AND independents AND the trigger.<br/><br/>Per-mismatch severity (the diff alone tells you the role):<br/>• Sync-group display at wrong Space → ERROR (sync genuinely failed)<br/>• Trigger at wrong Space → ERROR (user moved it mid-chain;<br/>  expectedEndState is now stale; we did NOT remediate)<br/>• Independent display at wrong Space → INFO (user swiped it<br/>  during our chain; we dropped the signal; surfaced for awareness)<br/>• Display vanished/appeared → ERROR (reconfig race)<br/><br/>Detection ≠ remediation. We log; we do NOT auto-retry.<br/>Then refresh state.lastActiveSpaces = actual so the next<br/>watcher fire diffs against truth. User re-swipes if they care.<br/><br/>Scope: runs ONLY on the sync-group path. NO_CHANGE just<br/>confirmed nothing changed; independent path didn't dispatch<br/>anything; reconfig path already rebuilt state from scratch.<br/>Runs BEFORE CLEAR so the gate stays closed during verify."]:::new

    POPUP["<b>Show popup on trigger display.</b><br/>The active Space index with names from the<br/>workspace name store. Auto-dismisses after popupDuration."]:::ui

    CLEAR["<b>Clear syncInProgress — re-arm.</b> <i>(simplified in v3)</i><br/>The last target verified (or timed out) and the<br/>end-of-chain verifier confirmed world matches expected.<br/>Set syncInProgress = false.<br/>No debounce wait — per-target observed-value writes<br/>already absorbed any echoes that may still arrive."]:::new

    UPDATE_BASELINE["<b>Update lastActiveSpaces baseline.</b><br/>Used by the independent-display path:<br/>set lastActiveSpaces = currentSpaces<br/>so the next watcher fire diffs against<br/>the post-switch state."]:::spoon

    DONE([<b>Watcher armed.</b><br/>Ready for the next event from either watcher.]):::terminal

    %% ============================================================
    %% ENTRY PATH 2 — DISPLAY RECONFIG → SCREEN WATCHER (new in v3)
    %% ============================================================

    RECONFIG([<b>Display layout changes.</b><br/>Monitor plugged/unplugged, lid open/close,<br/>dock/undock, displays rearranged in System Settings,<br/>resolution change.]):::user
    SW["<b>Screen watcher fires our callback.</b> <i>(new in v3)</i><br/>hs.screen.watcher invokes our Lua callback.<br/>Distinct from spaces-watcher — this fires on layout change,<br/>not on Space change."]:::macos
    SW_DEBOUNCE["<b>Coalesce burst.</b> <i>(council fix, new in v3)</i><br/>hs.screen.watcher fires 2-5× per real reconfig event<br/>as macOS settles geometry. Schedule the rebuild via<br/>hs.timer.doAfter(~250 ms); cancel and re-arm on<br/>subsequent fires within the window. One rebuild per<br/>real reconfig instead of one per fire."]:::new

    RECONFIG_GATE_ENABLED{"<b>Is SpacesSync enabled?</b><br/>If not, return — same logic as the swipe path."}:::decision
    RECONFIG_SKIP[/"<b>Return — SpacesSync is off.</b>"/]:::terminal

    RECONFIG_BAIL_GATE{"<b>Was a sync chain in flight?</b><br/>If yes, its targets may have just disappeared<br/>or shifted positions — we need to abort cleanly."}:::decision
    BAIL_CHAIN["<b>Abort the in-flight chain.</b><br/>Bump chainGeneration so any captured closure bails on next tick.<br/>Set syncInProgress = false.<br/>Stop ALL chain-owned timers (pollTimer + pendingSyncTimer +<br/>watchdog). Track them in a single chainTimers list so this<br/>is one cleanup call, not per-timer.<br/>Refresh state.lastActiveSpaces = hs.spaces.activeSpaces.<br/>(Without this, a partial chain leaves Frankenstein baseline:<br/>some targets have post-poll observed values, others have<br/>pre-chain values — the next watcher fire would diff wrong.)<br/>Log at info: 'Reconfig during chain — aborting.'"]:::new

    REBUILD_MAP["<b>Rebuild position map.</b><br/>Re-read hs.screen.allScreens, sort by frame x then y,<br/>reassign position numbers in reading order.<br/>Update positionToUUID, uuidToPosition, totalScreens."]:::new

    REFRESH_BASELINE["<b>Refresh lastActiveSpaces.</b><br/>The set of UUIDs has likely changed.<br/>Re-snapshot from current state so the next<br/>spaces-watcher fire has a valid baseline to diff against."]:::new

    VALIDATE_CONFIG["<b>Validate syncGroups against new layout.</b><br/>For each position N referenced in syncGroups,<br/>check N ≤ totalScreens. If any reference is now<br/>out of range, log a warning so the user knows<br/>their config refers to a display that's not connected."]:::new

    STATUS_HUD["<b>Show status HUD on main display.</b><br/>'SpacesSync: display layout changed.'<br/>The user knows we noticed and adapted.<br/>Without this, reconfig would be silent."]:::ui

    %% ============================================================
    %% EDGES — entry path 1 (swipe)
    %% ============================================================

    U --> OS --> W --> GATE_ENABLED
    GATE_ENABLED -- no --> SKIP_DISABLED
    GATE_ENABLED -- yes --> GATE_RUNNING

    GATE_RUNNING -- "yes — chain polling" --> DROP
    GATE_RUNNING -- "no — idle" --> DIFF --> FIND
    FIND -- no --> NO_CHANGE --> DONE
    FIND -- yes --> LOOKUP --> GROUP

    GROUP -- no --> INDEPENDENT --> POPUP
    GROUP -- yes --> LOCK --> COMPUTE_EXPECTED --> SYNCNEXT --> DISPATCH --> POLL --> VERIFY
    VERIFY -- yes --> OBSERVED_WRITE
    VERIFY -- "no — timeout" --> DROPPED_LOG --> OBSERVED_WRITE
    OBSERVED_WRITE --> MORE
    MORE -- yes --> SYNCNEXT
    MORE -- no --> POPUP

    POPUP -- "independent path:<br/>(no gotoSpace dispatched →<br/>no chain to clear)" --> UPDATE_BASELINE --> DONE
    POPUP -- "sync-group path:<br/>(chain finished →<br/>verify, then clear)" --> VERIFY_END_STATE --> CLEAR --> DONE

    %% ============================================================
    %% EDGES — entry path 2 (reconfig)
    %% ============================================================

    RECONFIG --> SW --> SW_DEBOUNCE --> RECONFIG_GATE_ENABLED
    RECONFIG_GATE_ENABLED -- no --> RECONFIG_SKIP
    RECONFIG_GATE_ENABLED -- yes --> RECONFIG_BAIL_GATE
    RECONFIG_BAIL_GATE -- yes --> BAIL_CHAIN --> REBUILD_MAP
    RECONFIG_BAIL_GATE -- no --> REBUILD_MAP
    REBUILD_MAP --> REFRESH_BASELINE --> VALIDATE_CONFIG --> STATUS_HUD --> DONE

    %% ============================================================
    %% DESIGN INTENT — what v3 changes vs. v0.2
    %% ============================================================

    DESIGN["<div style='text-align: left;'><b>Design intent — v3 verify-based redesign</b><br/><br/><b>The goal:</b> only human-initiated swipes trigger sync. Our gotoSpace echoes must not cause secondary syncs. Plus: the system should fail loudly when something is genuinely wrong.<br/><br/><b>How v3 achieves it:</b><br/>• <b>Per-target verification via polling.</b> Each gotoSpace is followed by a poll loop that waits for hs.spaces.activeSpaceOnScreen(target) to match the expected Space ID, with a pollTimeout fallback. Replaces the fragile fixed switchDelay.<br/>• <b>Per-target observed-value baseline writes.</b> After each poll-verify, we read activeSpaceOnScreen one more time and write the OBSERVED value into lastActiveSpaces (Q1 resolution; F-010 §6.2). Echoes diff to no-change naturally — no debounce window needed. The observed-value formulation cannot poison the baseline if macOS drops a dispatch (the baseline reflects reality, not optimism).<br/>• <b>syncInProgress gate, narrow.</b> Suppresses watcher fires during the in-flight polling window. Clears immediately after the end-of-chain verifier — no debounce padding.<br/>• <b>Screen watcher as second entry path.</b> hs.screen.watcher fires on display layout changes; we rebuild the position map, refresh the baseline, validate the config, and show a status HUD. No more silent breakage on monitor unplug.<br/>• <b>Hard block on missing Accessibility at :start.</b> hs.spaces.gotoSpace and hs.eventtap both require Accessibility permission. If revoked or never granted, :start fails loudly with an alert; no silent broken state.<br/><br/><b>What v3 drops vs. v0.2:</b><br/>• ⊖ Fixed switchDelay (0.3 s × N) → variable polling, bounded by pollTimeout.<br/>• ⊖ debounceSeconds (0.8 s) → eliminated entirely. Per-target observed-value writes absorb echoes by keeping lastActiveSpaces matched to macOS truth.<br/>• ⊖ Fixed ~1.7 s ignore window for 4 monitors → typical case ~2.3 s (numTargets × ~750 ms), driven by real settle not arbitrary clock. Worst case (every dispatch times out): numTargets × pollTimeout = 6 s for 4 displays. Trade-off: typical ≈ v0.2; pathological worse; correctness much better.<br/>• ⊖ Static position map → actively maintained via screen watcher.<br/>• ⊖ Silent Accessibility failure → loud hard block.<br/><br/><b>What v3 still accepts:</b><br/>• ⚠ Real user swipes inside the chain polling window are still dropped — polling doesn't queue them. Window typical ≈ v0.2's; pathological worse (see DROP node math). Bounded by actual macOS settle, not an arbitrary ceiling. User re-swipes if needed.<br/>• ⚠ If macOS drops a gotoSpace and we can't verify within pollTimeout, we log warning and continue. No automatic retry. User re-swipes; that's the recovery.<br/><br/><b>Failure modes that loudly tell the user something is wrong:</b><br/>• ✅ :start with Accessibility revoked → alert + abort<br/>• ✅ syncInProgress stuck → watchdog clears it, logs at error level<br/>• ✅ gotoSpace verification timeout → warning log per affected target<br/>• ✅ Display reconfig → status HUD + log<br/><br/><b>Open follow-up tasks (filed in OmniFocus, not blocking):</b><br/>• Per-display 'currently driving' set to replace global syncInProgress (multi-group correctness)<br/>• Stage Manager / fullscreen Spaces support<br/>• Multi-changed-display handling<br/>• macOS 16 (Tahoe) re-verification — F-010 is macOS-15-specific<br/>• Reduce Motion regime — F-010 didn't measure with animations off<br/>• Heavy-load regime — F-010 ran on quiet system</div>"]:::designbox
    classDef designbox fill:#1f1d0d,stroke:#d4a853,color:#f0e8c8,text-align:left
